messages.content: **8. Point 4: On Fate**

Intuition experiences a peculiar sensation of watching his own body, without his input, walk into the Catarina Tower Hospital Room. It then collapses to the ground, and he then regains control of his body. He's back in Arctica, for the immediate time being.
"Ha ha ha! What a great escape, Intuition! Not only did you get sent to a courtroom, you flawlessly escaped from its clutches!"
"Perhaps is a good time to meet my Mom in Elvith, and tell her all about my amazing stories this past week!"
"I like.... her..... right.....?"
"WAIT"
"Is that tied up guy still there"?

It is also worth noting, now that Intuition is fully up, that several things about this room have changed. The tied up guy is no longer there. The unconscious body of Horatius Kyodu is. There is also a piece of paper on the ground, and a noose tied up and hung from the ceiling.
"ITS HORATIUS! HI HORATIUS!"
Intuition decides to pick up the note, and put it in his pocket.
"I'm going to my mom's house? Wanna come?"
"Oh... she's not conscious, are they?"
"Well, when life gives you lemons, you make lemon scented swords"!
Intuition picks up Horatius's body.

The piece of paper has the following scrawled on it in marker:

NEKONEOKNENKONKENOKENEKOENONKOKNOKNKONEONEKEEKENONOKOKNOENOONEOKNENEKKONEOKKEONNENOOEOOEN...

It goes on like that. There appears to have been text under it, but it has been rendered unreadable.

Horatius wakes up.
Intuition continues to drag Horatius's body to his mom's house.
No.
((#horatius-overdrive attempt it here if you will))
Erica suddenly wakes up in a different place, lying on her side.
I check if I have my PDA.
You can feel that you do.
I open it and check the #earth-gc history.

“Okay. I guess you’re lying down in a position that makes doing that covertly feasible. Try not to fuck with anything happening around you, okay? I don’t want the mechanics to get any more convoluted just yet.”
Erica feels a little sluggish.
Huh? What do you mean?

Someone enters the room.
Madakoe’s voice can be heard saying “Shit. I fucked that up, then.”
“Not the present me. Ignore him.”
Oh. I lay still.
The rest of Erica's reaction occurs as before.
I wait until Erica leaves, and Rikarasu is alone with Geloto to listen to that conversation.
Well, not Erica. This is clearly some pathetic imposter. For future reference, let's dub her Efainda. A failed clone of my brilliance.
Wow.
((What is happening))
((Geloto leaves too right?))
Yes.
I get up and enter the computer room.
"Okay, coast is clear now. That's the last thing that happens in this central room."
Yeah. But where did Efainda even come from? Was she a literal clone or something? I try to find a way to open the device she woke up in.
John abruptly shows up in the computer room. "Went.... huh?"
"Oh. You're... here? Where is this?" He looks around.
Oh, he's still here. Well, I guess Efainda was useful for *something* at least. "Alright, John, you're my servant now."
"You need a better name though, I don't like this one." What kind of fantasy name is John? "What are your talents?"
Oh, and Madakoe. How did you teleport us in the first place?
Madakoe materializes the following diagram.
"You get it now?"
"Getting your PDA back took a lot of exertion on my part. I probably won't be able to fuck with things for a bit."
((attached image))
Oh, so we've skipped having to waste time back on Earth? That's good. There's nothing I really need back there. But how did you send Efainda and Rikarasu to that place in the sky?
Madakoe points to a computer.
"You should be able to just turn that one on now."
I turn it on.
It lights up on what resembles a browser window, currently on a profile page of Klaud Reaction.
“Okay, that’s weird, but not what I meant. The desktop should have something if you minimize this.”
I minimize it.
A file on the desktop named LINKED_LOCS.
I click it.

It opens to a menu with the following options.

- origin
- montanatest 
- capitaltapsite 
- origin_ext
- earth
- burdltwoodsWIP
“montanatest is here. Origin is that flying vessel.”
How do I sent Efainda and Rikarasu there? Oh, and I guess Geloto can go too for now. I'll just have to bring him back before he gets himself killed. That should fix everything.
“It’s going to happen regardless.”
The computer sparks with electricity for a moment, highlighting origin_ext. Then it returns to normal.
“The dumbest contrivance of all time.”
Okay, now I count the seconds until Geloto has left Rikarasu and Efainda's stupid feud. Then, I try to teleport him back.
((What happens if I send messages in the GC))
((Can I read Rikarasu's current message?))
((i have 1984ed that can’t happen))
((Got it))
((To which one though))
((I asked for 2 things))
“This terminal can send things from here to elsewhere.”
“Only that.”
Oh. What? Well, go back in time again. The whole point was to keep Geloto as my servant. I'll do it right this time.
“If you went back again, you wouldn’t be able to do anything. It would be like acting as a spectator.”
“You were able to go back to the presence of your other self because you were *already here*.”
Well, that's cheap. And lazy. Resurrect him!

“This isn’t Q&A, where the time travel is arbitrary and inconsistent because [spoiler]. And bringing someone who has died back isn’t possible. You can check with all the magic experts around here. None of them have figured that out.”

I sit back in my chair and stare at the computer for a moment. …Well, I'll figure it out. I'm special, after all. You can officially put Bringing Back The Dead on my list of goals. I'm not like that Efainda girl. I get shit done easily. Not to imply that I would refuse to follow your plot, of course. I can multi-task just fine. Now, just let me know where you want me to go, and I'll go right ahead and do that.
“You…”
“Yeah. It’s fine. …First things first, you’ll want to head to the house portion of this building. It’s one of those dumb minor things that come up later.”
((I am ending tthe session here muahahaha))
((FUCK))
((you may get in a last word if you like))
((I really wanted to respond to Rikarasu with a transcript of her conversation with Bardle, followed by "I win"))
I head upstairs.
"Your father's 'office', so to speak, should be over there." Madakoe points to a room on the first floor.
I enter the room he points to.
((SPOILERS))

This looks like a normal office. It's identical to its counterpart in reality if you'd ever entered there, with one exception. There's an incredibly ostentatious sword hilt (bladeless!) left on the table.
"You should probably take that."
I take the sword hilt. Is that all?
"Yeah, that would be it. Nothing else to do in this building."
Are you sure?
"Not gonna force you to leave this building without doing anything else. Just saying that there's nothing else directly plot relevant you haven't seen."
How soon will we need this?

"I dunno, it's just one of those things. Like, you get something that seems like its completely irrelevant, but then it comes up at a pivotal moment. Like Problem Sleuth. I will say that it's useless by itself, but that shouldn't be an issue."

Well, if it’s not gonna come up soon, I could just leave it here in storage for now. This is my home, after all. It’s best to not let important items be stolen by lunatics like Rikarasu. That’s my explanation. I put the hilt back down.
((Have I caught up to the gc yet))
((yeah sure we can say that the mental breakdown took  up enough time))
((The mental breakdown was before the time travel actually))
((yeah sure we can say that erica wastes enough time arguing with her brain ghost))
"Erica."
Yes?
"Are you actually serious? Is this a joke?"
Why wouldn’t I be serious?

"This building has already been entered by five other people, of which a single one never made an attempt on your life. And that was just because he was fucking asleep. How confident are you in its security?"
Well, it’s my home. I’ll just make it secure when I have more servants. That reminds me.
The channel is currently **unlocked**.
EF: @RE "I just got hours of lecturing on how I shouldn’t kill her and now some fucking guy is just gonna show up and do it? Come on." - Geloto LeMat
EF: @RE "I am not a guy, and I am not going to kill her." - Rikarasu Endo(Who is a liar!!!!)
EF: @RE "Do you know where she went?" - Rikarasu Endo(Dumb stupid moron who is a liar)
EF: @RE "No." - Geloto LeMat
EF: @RE "Ugh." - Rikarasu Endo(She’s definitely wishing she was working for me instead of being a liar rn!!!!!)
EF: @RE "Do you know where I could find a… forked twig? As in, a Y-shapes stick or branch ." - Rikarasu Endo(dumb stupid question a dumb stupid person would ask. She’s also a liar)
EF: @RE "Oh, man, that bullshit? Hang on." - Geloto LeMat
EF: @RE "Here. You can keep it, I don’t really need this anymore." - Geloto LeMat(Does everything for this liar, who is useless without him and does not deserve him)
EF: @RE "Uh… I appreciate it." - Rikarasu Endo(clearly understanding how pathetic and terrible and pathetic she is)
EF: @RE I win.
BM: Okay first of all who are all of you
BM: And second of all possible messages to send to this seemingly public communication channel, why are you posting the logs of a separate conversation?
EF: You wouldn’t get it

EF: I proposed this in the other group chat, when this one was inactive, but I am giving you all one chance to join my party of main characters. Except Rikarasu, Klaud, and Viotto who are all psychopathic lunatics who should not be trusted
EF: Someone else will have to provide the meeting location though because last time only Rikarasu showed up and she tried to murder me. I will not take that risk again. I am too essential for that.
EF: @HK You specifically must come. Now.
EF: @EA You too.
The channel is currently **locked**.
John IS still here.
Why aren’t any of them taking the offer? This should at least be completely within the rules, right?

"Well, you ruled out three of them. Horatius probably doesn't like you, Joliene would not be of any help to you, and Intuition would be an active detriment. About the only person left is like, Voreverl. She might show up."
Why would Horatius not like me?
"Who knows? It's as inexplicable as anyone not liking you."
Exactly. Seems like contrived writing. What’s his @?
"HK. It's weird that those initials keep coming up."
They do?

"I mean, there's Horatius Kyodu. There's the video game Hollow Knight, the location of Hong Kong... Hav Kerloe and Harriet Kadin. It's just one of those minor things, y'know? Like how everyone keeps fucking mentioning fate or some synonym."
That makes sense. What’s Voreverl's @?
"It's VL. They're all initials. But if you're wondering which one is the PDA Voreverl is using, it's EA, for reasons that are really dumb."
see attached
Oh, EA is Voreverl? Interesting.
They’re not responding to a *clear* prompt. This is getting ridiculous. Can you make them answer somehow, Madakoe?
"Not really. This isn't a matter of them not seeing it, they just don't want to respond. And I can't just control people's actions. That would be problematic."
Well, then don’t control a person. Just send them a message.
"That would probably be a moot point right now. Sorry."
Why?
"I guess by technicality you already did the next section on Earth? But I think it would be super boring for you to wander around with the goal of meeting Voreverl when Voreverl isn't even here."
Oh. What?
So… Does that mean I’m the only one awake here right now?

"Maybe? The chronology's a little weird. I just know you won't be able to meet Voreverl before she stops being here. Whether you'll also return to Earth is... I guess arbitrary. I mean, do you want to stay here the whole time?"
Of course I do. Is Rikarasu awake right now?
"No."
Where is she?
"Japan."
No, I mean her body.
"High up."
She’s still in that place Efainda was? I head back to the computer room.
"Are you going to like, kill her unconscious body. Or something."
No, of course not. I’m not a murderer. I open the computer back up and select origin.
"This literally wasn't my fault, to be clear. You just decided to do that."
What? Is something bad going to happen?
Erica enters the void, finishing the chapter. By which I mean. Retroactively Erica's weird Transfer Trick from before didn't count as a chapter and now she's finished the chapter
((Which chapter))
((Chapter 8))
The fourth floor contains seven doors spread evenly around its perimeter, one being the one Rikarasu entered it from. ((idk if viotto is still?? following????????))
((@Viotto Entenmann hi))
*She gently puts down Erica, opens the door closest to the left of her, and looks in.*
There's nothing in here but a small closet sized space with an arcane symbol drawn on the ground. ((sorry i am not going to do much while i dont know if bloop is here))
((yeah i'm hoping he comes in the next four hours))
((I'm so, so sorry))
((I just slept through my alarm because I was up too late. No excuse))
((it's okay i've done worse by like three hours))
"I doubt you'll find anything but symbolism in there."
((is Viotto with me right now))
((I would assume so))
"This arcane symbol is likely a teleportation rune. I do not know how to operate it, but we may need to step on it, or to read it aloud somehow."
Viotto sighs. "Stepping. It's activated by entering the room."
"Okay."
*She looks at him.* "Will you be accompanying me through here?"
"Do you have any idea where you're going? Because I certainly don't. I especially don't wish to follow if you're ransacking *tombs.*"
"I do not."
"How did you reach this airship, and what do you possibly plan to do here? As I indicated, staying appears to be a poor use of your time."

"As I've already said, this airship has kidnapped me every time I've had the *pleasure* of coming on board," he drawls. "But staying is as good a use of my time as leaving if you're entering a dank prison full of decomposing bodies. At least up here, I have airflow."
"I was told you were familiar with this tomb."
"And I rejected that characterization."
"These doors presumably all lead to different areas. I would rather take a gamble than remain trapped here. I may very well appear in a town perfectly safely."
"Do you have any way to communicate with anybody on-ground?"
"If I had that, I would certainly have better discussion company right now, wouldn't I?"
*She bends down over Erica and searches her body.*
Viotto looks to the side haughtily.
This *girl* really did remind him of his father.
((This guy should've died instead of Erica))
((say that to my face))
((i've never met Viotto sorry))
((roll investigation for the fucking body search ??))
There's nothing of note on Erica's body.
"Nothing."
"Perhaps I should search it as well, in case you missed something."
"That will not be necessary,.Viotto R. Entenmann."
"Can you look out at the ground? I want to make a note of any features that could identify this vessel's current location before I depart."
"So you can push me off? No, I think I'll let you do the honors."
"...So you can push me off?"

"If it wasn't clear, girl, you haven't done anything to earn my trust in any capacity. While I have provided literal, physical evidence of my life's work, offered materially useful information, and ensured *your* safety."
"This is not an equal-footing dispute. You check the ground."
He considers flashing his AVMA card again.
*She pulls open the door to the right of her (as in, two away from the one she previously opened, which was one away from the one she came through).*
This also looks like. The same. But the symbol is somewhat different
"None of them will take you home, child."
"Why are you taunting an unconscious girl?"
*She picks up Erica's body and places it down onto the symbol within the closet she just opened.*
"I'm not taunting anybody. What I said was eminently true and useful. How can your perception of the world around you be so warped?"
Erica's body fcuking vanishes
*She speaks with scorn.* "My perception of the world is not warped."
Viotto's shoulders untense slightly.
"That may not include my witnessing of teleportation."
Viotto speaks sarcastically. "Oh, don't begin to doubt your eyes now! We wouldn't want *that,* would we?!"
He considers stepping into the portal-elevator after the body, but decides he would be better off waiting.
"What are you talking about?"
*She steps out of the room with the seven doors and essentially lies down on the floor, with her head peering over the edge to the ground.*
Viotto walks over, and eases himself to the ground next to her.
"You know, things could be a lot worse. I can tell you have the capacity to understand your mistakes and work off of them."
*She ignores him and tries to make out any figures or structures below.*
"What's your name, girl?"
He prods her shoulder.
"My name is Fainda Shinjitsu. Stop distracting me."
"Fainda..."
"This is very symbolic. You looking down on the world from above, as if you play no part in it."
"That feeling of being absolved from responsibility... it's addicting, isn't it?"
"No."
He's surreptitiously looking at a notebook sticking out of his pocket.

"Well, responsibility... it comes for us all in the end. Not many people seem to be aware of that, recently. But to extend my metaphor, what comes for you, Fainda, is 'withdrawal.' Somebody there to wean you off... can't you appreciate the potential there?"
He awaits a response to the audience prompt.
"No?"

He continues.
"Ah, and there, you see, lies the catch. Why would anyone wish to even leave? You said it wasn't addicting just now, and yet, there are many types of addictions - to water, to food, to shelter. Addiction carries a negative connotation, sure, but I suppose I need to impress this upon you - this drug has negative *effects.* For, see where it has gotten you - you have failed to claim responsibility for those around you, and I know..." He considers the adjustment. "I know you have seen the repercussions recently. You have nobody left to even fight. And soon, I may be gone as well."
((sciipe can she see anything))
((shut up scipe))
((is she just looking. at the ground below))
((yeah))
That is the ground, far below. The corpse of not the famous bard from Q&A cannot be seen because it's too far away.
((so is there ANYTHING there. like a specific pattern of trees or))
*She gets up to her feet again.*

"But in spite of that, here we are, eh? Relying on the future too much... that's the very thing which I criticize. That's the very thing addicts do, when they say they'll quit 'someday'. To rely on my future loss of ability to assist you, it would be... to fall into that very same pattern of thinking. So, let's talk about the *now.* Right now, I am-"
"Please, Fainda, there's nothing for you to do back there."
"Viotto R. Entenmann, at no point have I failed to claim responsibility for anybody around me."
"A girl died under your supervision."
"And so did she die under yours."
"And who do you suppose took responsibility for it?"
"Shall we take a tally?"
"I seek the truth, and that is my sworn duty. I cannot be expected to account for and solve every single problem that could occur."
"What would you say your own 'responsibility' is? What is your goal in life?"
"To teach, and indeed, to learn."
"Sometimes, I feel as if I learn more from my audience members than they from me... haha."
"Perhaps you can understand that yours is rather similar to mine, then."

"I am not bound to pro-actively prevent crime, or to prevent sudden, unpredictable medical malady, or to take responsibility for all that I am asked to. A detective detects, and they work to help others when it serves the cause of their own detecting."

"Looking at the ideology at play seems purposeless here. You are avoiding reality. There was a body in my care, I dealt with it. There was a body in *your* care, you placed it somewhere entirely unknown to either of us. Does that seem like an effective result to you?"
"That location is only unknown until we follow her there."
"I consider that an effective result."
*She steps back into the room with the 7 doors.*
"And, indeed, how long you will stay a drug addict is unknown until you go to rehab. But perhaps there was a better solution to begin with."
Viotto follows with a bitter expression on his face.
"This is an instant method of transportation. Your analogy is broken."
"What would the 'better solution' even be? To kill the drug addict?"
"To not become addicted in the first place."
"Erica was already dead, and that was your fault as much as it was mine."
"If you had not fled, I could have prevented anything from happening to her."
"You, too, could have, with your medical knowledge."
"Would you like to explain how?"
"Perhaps John decided placed her under a curse. We could have fended him off. Perhaps she suddenly began to choke. We could have saved her."
"You know not even enough to guarantee her life is unrecoverable."
"I am not the one who made that assessment, yes. It was the potent magic-user!"
*She steps onto the symbol that she had placed Erica's body onto before.*
"Ah, fuck."
The situation is lost.
*She's sure he'll follow, probably.*
The chapter ends.

Some more uneventful chat occurs.

The moment the boat docks, Horatius wakes up back in Arctica in Neko's place again. Unlucky break.
They instantly jolt to awareness and look around. Where's the note they left behind? Is it in the same place they left it? Has anyone picked it up or read it?
Intuition Overdrive is currently in the process of reading it. ((channel creation one second))
He loses interest in the paper??? I guess???? #horatius-overdrive
Intuition drags Horatius's body to his mother's house to talk about his new "friend".
What
Intuition drags Horatius's body to his mother's house to talk about his new "friend".
Intuition is going to attempt to drag the body of Horatius Kyodu. Horatius, your response?
Horatius tries to punch him in the face really really hard.
((roll to hit))
Miss.
((I love how Horatius being fucking terrible at hand to hand is just coincidentally a consistent character trait))
"Hi Horatius! Can you come to my Mom's house?"
"Why the fuck would I do that!? What do you want!?"
"I was going to my mothers to talk about everything that has happened today! And you were on the ground, so....."
"You were practicing spelling, I see?"
Intuition holds up the note.
"But for note, I think its supposed to be spelt, N-E-C-O, not N-E-K-O!"
The note has had its original text scrawled over in marker. It reads NEKONEOKNENKONKENOKENEKOENONKOKNOKNKONEONEKEEKENONOKOKNOENOONEOKNENEKKONEOKKEONNENOOEOOEN... and so on.
Horatius turns pale at the sight of it. "Okay, okay, okay, look. Whatever. Fine. I'll go to your fucking house, on one condition. You don't tell anyone about th-... What?"
"Wait, *what?*" They stare at the note. Their guard drops completely.
"Did you do this??"
"I would NEVER spell Neko's name wrongly like that!"

"That- I didn't-" They continue staring at it in confusion, before finally adopting an expression of resignation. "You know what? Sure, today's your lucky day. I don't feel like sticking around here at the moment, and your house sounds like as good a place as any to get away from this one." Horatius sighs. "Lead the way, as long as you're not gonna kill me, I guess."
"Did you see a person who was tied up over here recently? He had horns."
"Seeing by that thingamiajig over there," Intuition points to the rope up there. "He was untied."
"Huh..." Horatius looks around the room. The person with horns isn't there, is he?
"I saw him, but I don't know what happened to him."
"What do you mean, you saw him? What was he doing?"
"Well you can't do much when you are tied up."
"Wait, so you saw him before he was untied. Okay..." They frown. "And sometime after that, he just... left?" They're saying this more to themself than they are to Intuition.
"Then I went to Japan and got arrested for kicking a police officer!"
Facepalm. "Yeah, that sounds like you."
"Thanks for alerting the entire police force there to everyone involved in this mess, by the way. Real excellent work there."
"Prison arcs in Arctican puppet shows are always prevalent! Wouldn't you want one in real life?"
"Anyways," Intuition picks up the note. "Your secret that you are illiterate is safe with me. My mom can hook you up with some of my first-grade learning kit books."
Horatius laughs bitterly. "Sure. Thanks, dude."
Intuition eats the paper.
???? Horatius does not know how to react to this.
Intuition marches to Elvith with Horatius to his mom's house.
They reluctantly follow him.
Intuition Overdrive (and Horatius Kyodu) arrive at Intuition Overdrive's mother's house.
Intuition rings the doorbell.
No response.
Intuition opens the door.
Intuition decides to ram the door by flying into it at full force.
Okay okay the door is open wow
This is the house of Intuition Overdrive's mother.
Intuition's fucking phone rings. Not the PDA but the phone he canonically has.
Intuition picks up the phone.
Horatius looks around the house to see what it's like.
It's a modest dwelling. Not the type you'd expect of nobility but also far beyond the means of the poor.

*Hello? Intuition?*
((The phone is set loud enough for Horatius to hear so I don't have to do some weird channel bullshit))
This is the voice of Katrielle. You can't see her sprites because this is a phone conversation, obviously.
"H-hey.... m-mom...."
"Wh-where a-are you..."
Intuition is sweating at the palms.
*"Ah, I'm in the middle of some important work right now. I saw you on that show earlier. Really funny stuff."*
"Th-thank you."
"One of the show's guests Horatius Kyoudou, is with me! Uh, say hi Horatius."
Intuition promptly gives it to Horatius.
Horatius waves at the phone with a big smile before giving it back to Intuition.
Intuition frowns pitifully at Horatius for the first time.
*"I see. That's interesting. How did you convince him to go along with you?"*
"Him-" They blurt out, before shutting up again.
"She, He, They, We, uhl"
"Suicidal ideation. I found them next to a noose."
"A suicide note was written too. But it was overwritten. It had someone's name on it that I know well; Neko."
"I disposed of the paper."
Intuition is visibly shaking.
*"Intuition, you shouldn't talk so lightly about suicide. I'd feel awful if I acquired the Groverfield inheritance through such an unpleasant event."*
"I'm sorry. I'm sorry."
Horatius kind of awkwardly stands there. They're not sure whether to tell Intuition to stop bringing them up or if it would be a bad time to interject.
Intuition stares at Horatius, knowing that he may or may not have broken their promise.
They just sigh and shrug their shoulders, making a "who even cares anymore" face.
"well, well, I'm. You know about this world, it is supposed to be created, t-to go beyond the limits of this world, crime is a-another road to success?"
*"Oh, yes, sure. And it just wouldn't feel right if you didn't announce at every opportunity that you were doing crime, right?"*
"The end justifies the means? The ends justify the means? The ends justify the mean?"
Horatius ironically starts to look a little concerned for their new 'friend'.

*"That's the kind of pragmatism I married into this family for. It's really nice how you try to live up to and emulate them, regardless of your level of competence or what anyone says. I love that about you, honey."*
"Thank you, mom. Thank you mom. Mwah."
"Gotta love Intuition, the word of c-c-course."
*"Anyway, just calling to ask about that gentleman with the sword. You and he are friends, right? Have you seem him around?"*
Intuition slowly starts to question what the word intuition even means. Not that was was educated to know what that is.
"Isador dechai? Th-the last name I checked he was in-invading Skelt's quarters."
"Isn't Skelt the guy who was at that...?" Horatius trails off.
"Skelt. The guy from the Squad of Important Sons. The SiMpSons."
"Huh. Don't know those."

*"I see. So he's still in Elvith, maybe... well, I'll figure it out. It's good to know you're meeting new people! Those sorts of connections are what make things happen. I told you about how I met the queen, right? That's been really important for my ability to stay in the know."*
"Can you re-recall the story for me?"

*"Ah, it was back when I was at that women's academy. The one that's just a method of marrying off nobles. She's too many years my senior for us to have been contemporaries, but she visited often in my days there, trying to argue with the higher-ups or something. I reached out, and we've been friends since."*
"That's nice to hear."
((What is the queens name again))
((Is it neko or someone else))
((Zita Praxis))
((neko is the queens daughter))
Intuition wipes his eyes.
